{{Infobox rock |name=Ankaramite |type=Igneous |image= |caption= |composition=[[Mafic]]:[[pyroxene]], [[olivine]] and [[plagioclase]]. }} '''Ankaramite''' is [[volcanic rock]] type of [[mafic]] composition. It is a dark [[porphyritic]] variety of [[basanite]] containing abundant [[pyroxene]] and [[olivine]] [[phenocryst]]s.<ref name=Ortiz>http://rmcg.unam.mx/17-1/(3)Ortiz.pdf Luis Enrique Ortiz Hernández, ''An Arc Ankaramite Occurrence in Central Mexico,'' [[Revista Mexicana de Ciencias Geológicas]], volumen 17, número 1 2000, p. 34-44</ref> It contains minor amounts of [[plagioclase]] and accessory [[biotite]], [[apatite]], and [[iron oxide]]s.
Its [[Type locality (geology)|type locality]] is [[Ankaramy Be|Ankaramy]] in [[Madagascar]]. It was first described in 1916.<ref name=Ortiz/>
